Interface MathematicaElementTypes

public interface MathematicaElementTypes

This interface provides token types which are used by the Lexer and later by the parser. Some TokenSet's are defined which are used for the basic highlighter. Every TokenSet is then used to define a group of tokens which are highlighted in the same color. Check MathematicaSyntaxHighlighter. As a last part this interface

is used to define the IElementType's which are used to mark the AST during parsing. Since I use a Pratt parser where every token gets its own small parser (called parselet) most lexer token types have one or more corresponding parser element types which are then used as nodes in the AST tree.
